# We're writing an interactive madlib.

# First, we have to explain to the user
# what we're doing and invite them to play.

puts "This is Emily's Hello-World Madlib " +
	"generator! Welcome aboard!"
puts "What's your name?"
name = gets.chomp
puts	"Would you like to play, " + 
			name.capitalize + "?"
answer = gets.chomp
puts "Alright! Let's get started!"

# Now we'll collect the information for
# completing the madlib.

puts "Could you give me an adjective?"
adj1 = gets.chomp
puts "Thanks! Can you name a place?"
place1 = gets.chomp
puts "Great! How about another adjective?"
adj2 = gets.chomp
puts "Rad. A noun, please?"
noun1 = gets.chomp
puts "You're on a roll! Another adjective?"
adj3 = gets.chomp
puts "Whoops, one more!"
adj4 = gets.chomp
puts "Can you name a person?"
person1 = gets.chomp
puts "Let's mix things up with a verb now."
verb1 = gets.chomp
puts "We're almost done! Gimme a noun!"
noun2 = gets.chomp
puts "And one more!"
noun3 = gets.chomp
puts "Another adjective, if you don't mind."
adj5 = gets.chomp
puts "And another place!"
place2 = gets.chomp
puts "Final noun!"
noun4 = gets.chomp
puts "And how about a number?"
number1 = gets.chomp
puts "Name a liquid."
liquid1 = gets.chomp
puts "And name some music to wrap this up!"
music1 = gets.chomp

# Whew. That took forever. But now we can
# set up the actual madlib body using the
# responses gleaned from the user.

puts "Thanks, " + name.capitalize + "!" +
			" You've been great!"
puts "Are you ready for this?"
answer = gets.chomp
puts " Alright: here we go!"
puts " "
puts name.capitalize + "'s Long Day"
puts " "
puts "It’s been an " + adj1 + " day."
puts "Here at " + place1 + " I had some " +
	"trouble with a " + adj2 + " " + 
	noun1 + ", which kept me pretty " +
	adj3 + " for most of the morning. " +
	"I was almost " + adj4 + 
	" after dealing with that, but then " +
	person1 + " showed up and started " + 
	verb1 + " my " + noun2 + 
	" even after I told them not to! " + 
	"How rude! After that, my " +
	noun3 + " broke, and I had to make a " +
	adj5.upcase + " run to " + place2 + 
	" so I could buy a " + noun4 +
	" to fix it. That cost about " + 
	number1 + " more dollars than I thought" + 
	" it would. Finally, I’m settled back " +
	"in at " + place1 + ", kicking up my feet" +
	" and relaxing with a nice glass of " +
	liquid1 + " and " + music1 + 
	" on the radio. Much better!"
